<HEAD>Kemp Prepares Ethics Code for Housing Department</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Housing Secretary Jack Kemp says his agency is
developing a new code of ethics to prevent the type of scandals that
have plagued the Department of Housing and Urban Development in
recent months.
   ``My first order is to clean house, stem to stern,'' Kemp told a
committee of the National League of Cities on Friday.
   Federal and congressional investigators are looking at
allegations of fraud and mismanagement that may have cost the
government billions of dollars in HUD money.
   The actions occurred before Kemp took office earlier this year,
but much of his attention has been focused on cleaning up the
problem, he told the urban representatives.
   Kemp said his agency is putting the final touches on ``a program
of ethics'' that is intended to prevent future scandals. He did not
spell out the details.
