assets and liabilities. Copies of the documents were released by the
presidential palace.
   Mrs. Aquino's disclosure of her wealth was in fulfillment of a
promise she gave shortly after a military uprising ousted 20-year
ruler President Ferdinand Marcos in February 1986 and installed her
to power.
   Marcos has been accused to stealing billions of dollars from the
Philippine treasury during his administration.
