<HEAD>Rockets Hit Norwegian Peacekeeping Headquarters</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Lebanon</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TYRE, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three rockets fired from the
Syrian-controlled Bekaa Valley in Lebanon hit the headquarters of
the Norwegian contingent of the U.N. peacekeeping force in southern
Lebanon Saturday, police reported.
   They said there were no casualties.
   Police said the Katyusha rockets were fired during artillery
exchanges between Arab guerrillas and units of Israeli troops and
their allied Lebanese militiamen in Israel's self-designated
