zone,'' a 6-to-10-mile deep border strip in south Lebanon.
   The Norwegian battalion's area of operation overlaps with the
zone, which Israel established as a buffer against cross-border
guerrilla raids into Israel's northern settlements.
   The 680-strong Norwegian battalion is part of the U.N.
peacekeeping force deployed in southern Lebanon since 1978.
   Other nations participating are Fiji, Finland, France, Ghana,
Ireland, Italy, Nepal and Sweden.
