<FIRST>r a AM-USOpen-Newspage     09-09 0257</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-US Open-Newspage,0264</SECOND>
<HEAD>Steffi Graf Wins U.S. Open Tennis Tournament</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steffi Graf won her third major tennis tournament
of the year Saturday, beating the heat and Martina Navratilova 3-6,
7-5, 6-1 in the U.S. Open final.
   The only blemish on the top seed's record in the four Grand Slam
events this year was a final-round loss to Arantxa Sanchez Vicario
in the French Open.
   ``It's very difficult to play in the four (major) tournaments and
do the best you can,'' Graf said. ``I'm very happy I won another
three.''
   The match, played in near 100-degree temperatures on the court,
ended with an ace on a second serve by Graf, who then sprinted to
the courtside boxes to hug her father. She also signaled to a group
of fans high in the stadium that had been chanting her name
throughout the 1-hour, 50-minute match.
   Graf, 20, has won seven of the last eight major tournament _ the
third woman to do so and first since Margaret Smith Court in 1969-70
_ while Navratilova hasn't won one since the 1987 Open, when she
beat Graf for the title.
   ``It was really just a matter of a couple of points here and
there,'' said Navratilova, who received an ovation. ``I'll keep
trying until those points go my way.''
   Graf, of West Germany, has won each of the Grand Slam titles
twice.
   Graf won $300,000 for her 11th tournament win this year.
Navratilova, 32, a native of Czechoslovakia who is now a U.S.
citizen, earned $150,000.
</TEXT>
