<HEAD>Baby Born on Flight Enroute to JFK</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A baby boy was born Saturday in the first-class
section of a New-York bound jumbo jet from London, police said.
   ``It's a first class baby,'' said Lt. Kevin Hassett of the Port
Authority police at John F. Kennedy International Airport.
   The boy was born at about 5:45 p.m. Saturday aboard a Kuwait
Airways' Boeing 747 while the plane was over Canada, Hassett said.
   The baby, which was delivered by two doctors aboard Flight 101,
