<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police gave a job application to an unarmed
bank security guard who chased and tackled a man later booked for
investigation of robbery Saturday, authorities said.
   ``He's the type of guy we're looking for,'' Sgt. Bob Grant said
of the Pinkerton guard, Aundra Spencer.
   A man walked into a Bank of America branch and handed a teller a
withdrawal ticket that read, ``This is a holdup,'' Grant said. The
